  <refnamediv>
    <refname>amd64</refname>

    <refpurpose>the SCAL/UX port to AMD 64/Intel IA-32e-based PCs</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <refsection>
      <title>Memory map</title>

      <para>Memory is laid out as follows:</para>

      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>0x0-0x00007fffffffffff</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>User address space</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>0xffff800000000000-0xffff810000000000</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Direct map of memory (1tb)</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>0xffffffff80000000-0xffffffffffffffff</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Kernel mappings</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>

      <para>The user-space address space is laid out specifically thus:</para>

      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term>0x0-0x8000</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Null mapping - always raises segmentation fault</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>0x400000</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Program load address</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>

        <varlistentry>
          <term>0x40000000</term>

          <listitem>
            <para>Dynamic linker load address</para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </refsection>
  </refsection>
